    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** standing as the clear offensive anchor. With a robust efficiency score of 87.42, **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a high-ceiling matchup against Young, where park factors and an elite 0.393 xwOBA provide the ideal environment to chase R and RBI accumulation. Joining him in the \"Strong\" start tier are **Trea Turner** (72.20) and **Kyle Schwarber** (70.37). Both **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** take advantage of a favorable 4.46 xERA from Houser; while **Trea Turner** faces a marginal drag from the opposing catcher\u2019s pop time, his premium leadoff spot ensures he remains our primary catalyst for the scarcity of stolen bases.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, who finished just shy of our 40.0 floor with a 39.38 score. While **Jerar Encarnacion** offers decent platoon potential against the left-handed S\u00e1nchez, the latter\u2019s 3.02 xERA proved too daunting to overcome, effectively capping the upside for **Jerar Encarnacion** relative to our game cap constraints. Meanwhile, **Colt Keith** (63.34) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (60.36) project as steady contributors, with **Colt Keith** seeing a significant bump from his #3 lineup placement. We remain wary of **Carson Benge** (56.03); while he offers a marginal start, his lower-third batting order against Mikolas keeps him at the bottom of our active rotation. We are currently monitoring **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, **Christian Yelich**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Luke Raley**, **Josh Smith**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** for future deployment as schedules align.",
